---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import BrandBranchesGrid from '../../components/BrandBranchesGrid.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE, MAIN_PHONE_TEL } from '../../data/branches';

const title = "Dacor Microwave Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "$89 dx waived. Dacor microwave repair SoCal, legacy DTL/DMW built-in + drawer units we still service. Samsung-owned since 2016. Honest scope.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/dacor-microwave-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Does Dacor still make microwaves, I can't find them on the new product site?",
    a: "Honest answer: <b>Dacor's modern US residential lineup focuses on ranges, cooktops, wall ovens, refrigerators, and dishwashers, microwaves are not a headline category today.</b> Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016 and streamlined Dacor's US portfolio around matched-suite luxury cooking. Some legacy Dacor microwaves are still in the field (DMW-series built-in, DTL-series countertop, DMR-series drawer from the mid-2000s through early 2010s), and we service those. For a <b>new</b> microwave in a Dacor-branded kitchen, the matched-suite modern answer is typically a Samsung Bespoke built-in or drawer, which shares parts-chain reciprocity with Dacor since the 2016 acquisition. See <a href='/brands/samsung-microwave-repair/'>Samsung microwave repair</a>."
  },
  {
    q: "What legacy Dacor microwaves do you actually service?",
    a: "We service the Dacor US residential microwaves that customers still have installed: <b>DMW-series built-in microwaves</b> (24/27/30 inch cabinetry-integrated, typically 2005-2014 vintage); <b>DTL-series countertop</b> (design-statement countertop from the Distinctive line); <b>DMR-series drawer microwaves</b> (early-generation drawer, pre-dating the current Sharp-OEM drawer architecture adopted across Wolf / Thermador / Miele); <b>DMW-2440 / DMW-2420 Discovery iQ</b> smart-built-in (early WiFi / app-connected units). Parts availability varies by model age, some common parts are still in Samsung / Dacor channel; serial-matched or unique parts on 10+ year units go factory-salvage or cross-reference through Samsung's modern parts catalog."
  },
  {
    q: "My DMW built-in died, is it worth repairing vs replacing?",
    a: "Depends on failure mode and unit age. For a <b>10+ year old DMW</b> with a magnetron failure, the economics often favor replacement, legacy Dacor microwaves carry premium pricing on dwindling parts inventory and the resale value doesn't justify the repair cost when a Samsung Bespoke built-in at comparable spec is available through the modern Dacor-Samsung parts chain. For a <b>5-8 year old DMW</b> with a simple failure (door switch, turntable motor, light socket), repair usually wins, parts are still available and labor is modest. We run the honest repair-vs-replace analysis during diagnostic and give you the real numbers, not the most-expensive-repair-possible pitch."
  },
  {
    q: "Dacor and Samsung parts-chain reciprocity, what does that actually do for me?",
    a: "Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016, and since then <b>parts supply chains have increasingly overlapped on newer (2018+) Dacor units</b> and on Samsung units of comparable vintage. For mechanical components, motor assemblies, LED modules, igniter sparks, oven temperature sensors, a backordered Dacor part often has a Samsung cross-reference with immediate stock, and vice versa. For older legacy Dacor microwaves (pre-2016), the reciprocity is thinner (the acquisition didn't retroactively unify pre-Samsung Dacor parts). Practical impact: the newer your Dacor microwave, the better your parts-availability odds; the older it is, the more likely we're sourcing from legacy inventory or recommending a Samsung Bespoke replacement."
  },
  {
    q: "Is there a modern Dacor drawer microwave like Wolf / Thermador / Miele?",
    a: "Not in Dacor's current US catalog. The <b>modern luxury drawer microwave category is owned by Sharp's OEM chassis</b>, which sells under three luxury brand names: Wolf ICBMODR, Thermador MD24WSS, Miele EDT-series. Dacor does not participate in that Sharp OEM drawer ecosystem. Earlier Dacor drawer microwaves (the DMR-series from the early 2010s) used Dacor's own drawer architecture, which is now out of production. If you want a matched-suite drawer microwave in a Dacor-branded luxury kitchen, the modern answer is one of the three Sharp-OEM-chassis drawers, or accept that Dacor's modern identity is range-and-cooktop-centric without a microwave flagship. See <a href='/brands/sharp-microwave-repair/'>Sharp drawer reference</a>."
  },
  {
    q: "What does Dacor microwave repair cost in LA?",
    a: "Residential diagnostic $89 waived with repair. Typical Dacor bands on <b>legacy DMW/DTL/DMR units</b>: magnetron $220–$400 (older units carry higher parts pricing on dwindling inventory); main control board $320–$560 (serial-matched on 10+ year units); door switch $100–$180; turntable motor $80–$140; light socket / bulb $40–$120; legacy DMR drawer linear actuator (if still sourceable) $280–$460; Samsung cross-reference where available can lower price by $40–$100 on compatible components. Honest repair-vs-replace analysis during diagnostic."
  },

    {
      q: "Where can I find the official Dacor manual or warranty information?",
      a: `For official Dacor documentation, warranty registration, and authorized service locator, visit <a href="https://www.dacor.com/service-and-support" rel="nofollow noopener" target="_blank">Dacor service & support</a>. Our technicians work independently of Dacor's factory service network - we're often faster and available same-day in Southern California.`
    },
  ];

const schemaJsons = [
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "LocalBusiness", "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair, Dacor Microwave Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical, "telephone": MAIN_PHONE_TEL, "priceRange": "$$$"
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "Service", "serviceType": "Dacor Microwave Repair (Legacy)",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "Dacor legacy microwave repair across LA, DMW built-in, DTL countertop, DMR drawer. Dacor modern US lineup does not headline microwaves; Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016 and matched-suite modern answer routes to Samsung Bespoke. Legacy units still serviced with honest repair-vs-replace analysis. $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "priceSpecification": { "@type": "PriceSpecification", "price": "89.00", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair" } }
  },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "FAQPage", "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({ "@type": "Question", "name": f.q, "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a } })) },
  { "@context": "https://schema.org", "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Dacor", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/dacor/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "Dacor Microwave Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">{schemaJsons.map((schema) => (<script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />))}</Fragment>
  <div class="call-banner"><div class="wrap"><span>Dacor microwave service?</span><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="phone-lg">{MAIN_PHONE}</a></div></div>

  <section class="hero"><div class="wrap">
    <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › Dacor › Microwave Repair</div>
    <h1>Dacor Microwave Repair</h1>
    <p class="lede">Dacor's modern US residential lineup centers on ranges, cooktops, wall ovens, refrigerators, and dishwashers, microwaves are not a headline Dacor category today. Samsung acquired Dacor in 2016 and streamlined the portfolio around matched-suite luxury cooking, so if you're buying a new microwave for a Dacor-branded kitchen the matched-suite modern answer is typically a Samsung Bespoke built-in or drawer (with parts-chain reciprocity to the Dacor service network). But legacy Dacor microwaves are still in the field, DMW built-in, DTL countertop, DMR drawer from the mid-2000s through early 2010s, and we service those honestly, with a clear repair-vs-replace analysis for older units. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.</p>
    <div class="hero-cta"><a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a><a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a></div>
    <ul class="hero-facts">
      <li><b>Legacy DMW / DTL / DMR series serviced</b>, pre-Samsung Dacor units still in the field</li>
      <li><b>Samsung-owned since 2016</b>, parts-chain reciprocity on 2018+ units</li>
      <li><b>Modern Dacor catalog does not headline microwaves</b>, Samsung Bespoke is the match</li>
      <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b>, waived when you authorize the repair</li>
    </ul>
  </div></section>

  <BrandBranchesGrid />

  <section class="trust-bar"><div class="wrap"><span>BHGS #A49573 · Insured</span><span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span><span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span></div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>What Dacor microwave repair costs in LA</h2>
    <table class="price-table">
      <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Waived with repair</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Magnetron (legacy DMW/DTL)</td><td>$220 – $400</td><td>Dwindling parts inventory premium</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Main control board</td><td>$320 – $560</td><td>Serial-matched on 10+ year units</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Door switch</td><td>$100 – $180</td><td>Safety interlock common failure</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Turntable motor</td><td>$80 – $140</td><td>Cross-fits newer platforms</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Light socket / bulb</td><td>$40 – $120</td><td>Common quick fix</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Legacy DMR drawer linear actuator</td><td>$280 – $460</td><td>If still sourceable</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Discovery iQ WiFi module</td><td>$160 – $260</td><td>DMW-2440 / DMW-2420 early smart</td></tr>
    </table>
    <p class="small">Related: <a href="/brands/dacor-oven-repair/">Dacor brand hub</a> · <a href="/brands/dacor-range-repair/">Dacor range / stove</a> · <a href="/brands/dacor-refrigerator-repair/">Dacor refrigerator</a> · <a href="/brands/samsung-microwave-repair/">Samsung microwave (modern matched-suite)</a> · <a href="/brands/samsung-range-repair/">Samsung range (parts-chain peer)</a> · <a href="/services/microwave-repair/">Microwave repair (service hub)</a> · <a href="/price-list/microwave-repair-cost/">Microwave repair cost</a>.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Honest positioning, modern Dacor is not a microwave brand</h2>
    <p>We believe in scope honesty: <b>Dacor's modern US identity is range + cooktop + wall oven + refrigerator + dishwasher</b>, not microwaves. Samsung's 2016 acquisition streamlined Dacor's catalog around matched-suite luxury cooking, and the modern microwave answer for a Dacor kitchen is a Samsung Bespoke built-in or drawer (with parts-chain reciprocity back to the Dacor service network). If you're doing a new build or renovation, we'll route you to the right modern product rather than forcing a legacy-Dacor microwave decision. If you already have a legacy DMW / DTL / DMR unit and you want to keep it working, we service those with honest repair-vs-replace economics, no pitch to over-invest in a 10-year-old microwave when replacement is the cheaper long-term answer.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Dacor microwave repair, frequently asked</h2>
    {faqs.map(f => (<details class="faq"><summary>{f.q}</summary><p set:html={f.a}></p></details>))}
  </div></section>

  <section id="book" class="cta-bottom"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Dacor microwave service? Call the branch closest to your home.</h2>
    <p>Same-day appliance repair in Los Angeles, Orange County, Ventura County. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
  </div></section>
  <a href={`tel:${MAIN_PHONE_TEL}`} class="float-call" aria-label="Call now">☎ Call {MAIN_PHONE}</a>
</Layout>

<style>
  :root { --red: #C8102E; --black: #0a0a0a; --gray: #f5f5f5; --border: #e2e2e2; --text: #1a1a1a; --muted: #6b6b6b; }
  body { color: var(--text); } .wrap { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 24px; } .wrap.narrow { max-width: 820px; }
  h1 { font-size: 2.4rem; line-height: 1.15; margin: 12px 0 20px; color: var(--black); }
  h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; margin: 0 0 16px; color: var(--black); }
  p { line-height: 1.65; margin: 0 0 14px; }
  .call-banner { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 10px 0; }
  .call-banner .wrap { display:flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .call-banner .phone-lg { color:#fff; font-weight: 800; text-decoration: underline; font-size: 1.05rem; }
  .hero { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 42px 0 56px; } .hero h1 { color: #fff; }
  .hero .lede { font-size: 1.06rem; color: #d7d7d7; max-width: 680px; }
  .hero .crumb { color: #9a9a9a; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 6px; } .hero .crumb a { color: #c9c9c9; text-decoration: none; }
  .hero-cta { display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin: 18px 0 24px; }
  .btn { display: inline-block; padding: 12px 20px; border-radius: 4px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; }
  .btn-primary { background: var(--red); color: #fff; } .btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: #fff; border: 1px solid #fff; }
  .hero-facts { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; color: #c9c9c9; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .hero-facts li { padding: 6px 0; border-top: 1px solid #222; } .hero-facts li:first-child { border-top: 0; }
  .trust-bar { background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 0; }
  .trust-bar .wrap { display: flex; gap: 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; justify-content: center; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600; }
  .section { padding: 56px 0; } .section.alt { background: var(--gray); }
  .price-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-top: 14px; background: #fff; }
  .price-table th, .price-table td { text-align: left; padding: 11px 12px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .price-table th { background: var(--black); color: #fff; font-weight: 700; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  .small { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.92rem; margin-top: 12px; }
  .faq { background: #fff; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 12px 16px; margin-bottom: 8px; border-radius: 4px; }
  .faq summary { font-weight: 700; cursor: pointer; padding: 4px 0; } .faq p { margin: 8px 0 0; }
  .cta-bottom { background: var(--black); color: #fff; padding: 48px 0; } .cta-bottom h2 { color: #fff; } .cta-bottom p { color: #c9c9c9; }
  .float-call { position: fixed; bottom: 18px; right: 18px; background: var(--red); color: #fff; padding: 14px 18px; border-radius: 40px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 700; box-shadow: 0 6px 18px rgba(0,0,0,0.28); z-index: 50; font-size: 0.95rem; }
  @media (max-width: 820px) { h1 { font-size: 1.9rem; } .float-call { padding: 11px 14px; font-size: 0.88rem; } .trust-bar .wrap { gap: 14px; font-size: 0.85rem; } }
</style>
